criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  FEV1 between 30 and 80% of the predicted normal values

          -  FEV1/FVC ratio < 70%

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with very severe COPD (GOLD IV);

          -  Patients that had a COPD exacerbations within the preceding 2 weeks of the baseline
             assessments;

          -  Significant hypoxemia at rest or during exercise (SpO2 <85%);

          -  Already following a rehabilitation program;

          -  Have physical limitations that compromises participation to a Tai chi and a
             conventional exercise program
